Benign solid and papillary epithelial tumors of the pancreas. A case report of a benign pancreatic tumor and its differential diagnosis is presented. The patient was a 31-year-old woman with a benign solid and papillary epithelial pancreatic tumor. Differentiation from a malignant tumor and from a hormonal active tumor was possible by the smooth boundaries and absence of contrast medium enhancement on CT. Exact diagnosis was found by laparatomy and histology.